Facing the possibility of a new indictment that includes racketeering charges, Atlanta Falcons quarterback Michael Vick will join his three co - defendants and agree this week to a plea deal with prosecutors in his federal dogfighting case, according to two people with knowledge of the case.
The assertion that Atlanta Falcons quarterback Michael Vick gambled on dogfighting appears to be a serious threat to his professional football career and freedom than the federal felony charges that he helped organize and run a dogfighting ring.
